fix:
boolean isAssignedOnceInLifetime() {
  Reference ref = getOneAndOnlyAssignment();
  if (ref == null) {
    return false;
  }

  boolean visited = new HashSet<String>();
  Stack<Statement> stack = new Stack<Statement>();
  stack.push(ref.getBasicBlock().entry);

  while(!stack.isEmpty()) {
    Statement statement = stack.pop();

    if (!visited.contains(statement.toString())) {
      visited.add(statement.toString());

      if(statement instanceof IfStatement) {
        IfStatement ifState = (IfStatement)statement;

        for (int i = 1; i < ifState.getSuccessors().length; ++i) {
          BasicBlock successor = ifState.getSuccessors()[i];

          if(successor != null && !successor.isUnreachable()) {
            stack.push(successor.entry);
          }
        }
      } else if (statement instanceof ExpressionStatement) {
        ExpressionStatement expStat = (ExpressionStatement)statement;

        if(expStat.expression instanceof Assign) {
          Assign assign = (Assign)expStat.expression;

          if(assign.getTarget() instanceof Local || assign.getTarget() instanceof Parameter) {

            if(visited.contains(assign.getTarget().getName())){
              continue;
            }else{

              String targetName = ((Local|Parameter)assign.getTarget()).getName();
              int indexOfVar = currentCompilationUnit.ast().findVariable(targetName).index;

              ArrayList assignments = currentCompilationUnit.findAllReferencesToVariable(indexOfVar);

                if(assignments.size() > 1) {
                  return false;

                 } 
              }
            }
          }
        } else if (statement instanceof ReturnStatement) {
          break;
        }
      }

    }

    if(ref.getBasicBlock() == ((ReturnStatement)statement).getReturnedExpression().getEnclosingBlock()) {
      return visited.size() == 1;

    } else if(ref.getBasicBlock().equals(((ReturnStatement)statement).getReturnedExpression().getEnclosingBlock().predecessors[0])) {
      return visited.size() <= 2;
    }
  }

  throw new RuntimeException("Failed to detect variable lifespan.");
}

issue_description:
The following code:

	// ==ClosureCompiler==
	// @compilation_level ADVANCED_OPTIMIZATIONS
	// ==/ClosureCompiler==
	var uid;
	function reset() {
		uid = Math.random();
	}
	function doStuff() {
		reset();
		var _uid = uid;

		if (uid < 0.5) {
			doStuff();
		}

		if (_uid !== uid) {
			throw 'reset() was called';
		}
	}
	doStuff();

...gets optimized to:

	var a;function b(){a=Math.random();0.5>a&&b();if(a!==a)throw"reset() was called";}b();

Notice how _uid gets optimized away and (uid!==_uid) becomes (a!==a) even though doStuff() might have been called and uid's value may have changed and become different from _uid.

As an aside, replacing the declaration with "var _uid = +uid;" fixes it, as does adding an extra "uid = _uid" after "var _uid = uid".

